14/06/2004
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Finance Minister Lyubomir Datsov said on Sunday (13 June) that Bulgaria plans to seek extra EU financial support to strengthen border security. Additional support will be requested also for budgetary issues during the first three years of Bulgaria's expected EU membership, 2007 to 2009. The additional funding would be used for new equipment used by the border guard and customs services.
Meanwhile, Economy Minister Lidia Shoulevais is in London, trying to boost foreign investment. She will participate in a business forum and a roundtable on outsourcing, stressing Bulgarian IT investment opportunities. (24 Chasa, Trud - 14/06/04; Mediapool - 13/06/04)
